{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":492,"text":"The two most likely largest inventions"},{"time":5126,"text":"of our generation"},{"time":7373,"text":"are the Internet and the mobile phone."},{"time":10566,"text":"They've changed the world."},{"time":12701,"text":"However, largely to our surprise,"},{"time":16216,"text":"they also turned out to be the perfect tools"},{"time":20614,"text":"for the surveillance state."},{"time":23764,"text":"It turned out that the capability"},{"time":26661,"text":"to collect data, information and connections"},{"time":30705,"text":"about basically any of us and all of us"},{"time":34923,"text":"is exactly what we've been hearing"},{"time":36736,"text":"throughout of the summer\nthrough revelations and leaks"},{"time":41343,"text":"about Western intelligence agencies,"},{"time":44434,"text":"mostly U.S. intelligence agencies,"},{"time":47460,"text":"watching over the rest of the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":50633,"text":"We've heard about these starting with the"},{"time":53831,"text":"revelations from June 6."},{"time":57517,"text":"Edward Snowden started leaking information,"},{"time":60586,"text":"top secret classified information,"},{"time":62890,"text":"from the U.S. intelligence agencies,"},{"time":64357,"text":"and we started learning about things like PRISM"},{"time":66826,"text":"and XKeyscore and others."},{"time":70093,"text":"And these are examples of the kinds of programs"},{"time":73198,"text":"U.S. intelligence agencies are running right now,"},{"time":77477,"text":"against the whole rest of the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":80993,"text":"And if you look back about the forecasts"},{"time":84701,"text":"on surveillance by George Orwell,"},{"time":88817,"text":"well it turns out that"},{"time":90935,"text":"George Orwell was an optimist."},{"time":93439,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":95919,"text":"We are right now seeing a much larger scale"},{"time":98619,"text":"of tracking of individual citizens"},{"time":100517,"text":"than he could have ever imagined."}]},{"cues":[{"time":104149,"text":"And this here is the infamous"},{"time":107684,"text":"NSA data center in Utah."},{"time":111528,"text":"Due to be opened very soon,"},{"time":114684,"text":"it will be both a supercomputing center"},{"time":117475,"text":"and a data storage center."},{"time":119612,"text":"You could basically imagine it has a large hall"},{"time":122505,"text":"filled with hard drives storing data"},{"time":124961,"text":"they are collecting."},{"time":127235,"text":"And it's a pretty big building."},{"time":129392,"text":"How big? Well, I can give you the numbers --"},{"time":131243,"text":"140,000 square meters --"},{"time":133265,"text":"but that doesn't really tell you very much."},{"time":135871,"text":"Maybe it's better to imagine it as a comparison."},{"time":139047,"text":"You think about the largest IKEA store"},{"time":141503,"text":"you've ever been in."},{"time":143250,"text":"This is five times larger."},{"time":146719,"text":"How many hard drives can you fit in an IKEA store?"},{"time":149795,"text":"Right? It's pretty big."},{"time":151802,"text":"We estimate that just the electricity bill"},{"time":154648,"text":"for running this data center"},{"time":156524,"text":"is going to be in the tens of millions of dollars a year."},{"time":159922,"text":"And this kind of wholesale surveillance"},{"time":162431,"text":"means that they can collect our data"},{"time":165167,"text":"and keep it basically forever,"},{"time":167170,"text":"keep it for extended periods of time,"},{"time":169679,"text":"keep it for years, keep it for decades."},{"time":172925,"text":"And this opens up completely new kinds of risks"},{"time":176304,"text":"to us all."},{"time":178250,"text":"And what this is is that it is wholesale"},{"time":181878,"text":"blanket surveillance on everyone."}]},{"cues":[{"time":186735,"text":"Well, not exactly everyone,"},{"time":188289,"text":"because the U.S. intelligence only has a legal right"},{"time":192317,"text":"to monitor foreigners."},{"time":194287,"text":"They can monitor foreigners"},{"time":196037,"text":"when foreigners' data connections"},{"time":198847,"text":"end up in the United States or pass\nthrough the United States."},{"time":202337,"text":"And monitoring foreigners doesn't sound too bad"},{"time":205121,"text":"until you realize"},{"time":207488,"text":"that I'm a foreigner and you're a foreigner."},{"time":210489,"text":"In fact, 96 percent of the planet are foreigners."}]},{"cues":[{"time":214275,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":215945,"text":"Right?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":217832,"text":"So it is wholesale blanket surveillance of all of us,"},{"time":222281,"text":"all of us who use telecommunications and the Internet."}]},{"cues":[{"time":226383,"text":"But don't get me wrong:"},{"time":228274,"text":"There are actually types\nof surveillance that are okay."},{"time":233500,"text":"I love freedom, but even I agree"},{"time":236529,"text":"that some surveillance is fine."},{"time":238808,"text":"If the law enforcement is trying to find a murderer,"},{"time":242711,"text":"or they're trying to catch a drug lord"},{"time":245813,"text":"or trying to prevent a school shooting,"},{"time":249417,"text":"and they have leads and they have suspects,"},{"time":251094,"text":"then it's perfectly fine for them\nto tap the suspect's phone,"},{"time":254811,"text":"and to intercept his Internet communications."},{"time":258167,"text":"I'm not arguing that at all,"},{"time":260105,"text":"but that's not what programs like PRISM are about."},{"time":262929,"text":"They are not about doing surveillance on people"},{"time":265814,"text":"that they have reason\nto suspect of some wrongdoings."},{"time":269018,"text":"They're about doing surveillance on people"},{"time":270695,"text":"they know are innocent."}]},{"cues":[{"time":274455,"text":"So the four main arguments"},{"time":276700,"text":"supporting surveillance like this,"},{"time":278852,"text":"well, the first of all is that whenever you start"},{"time":281087,"text":"discussing about these revelations,"},{"time":282982,"text":"there will be naysayers trying to minimize"},{"time":285275,"text":"the importance of these revelations, saying that"},{"time":287463,"text":"we knew all this already,"},{"time":289076,"text":"we knew it was happening, there's nothing new here."},{"time":292656,"text":"And that's not true. Don't let anybody tell you"},{"time":295871,"text":"that we knew this already,\nbecause we did not know this already."},{"time":301583,"text":"Our worst fears might have been something like this,"},{"time":305356,"text":"but we didn't know this was happening."},{"time":307307,"text":"Now we know for a fact it's happening."},{"time":310084,"text":"We didn't know about this.\nWe didn't know about PRISM."},{"time":312663,"text":"We didn't know about XKeyscore.\nWe didn't know about Cybertrans."},{"time":315569,"text":"We didn't know about DoubleArrow."},{"time":317519,"text":"We did not know about Skywriter --"},{"time":319667,"text":"all these different programs"},{"time":321362,"text":"run by U.S. intelligence agencies."},{"time":324603,"text":"But now we do."}]},{"cues":[{"time":327632,"text":"And we did not know"},{"time":329798,"text":"that U.S. intelligence agencies go to extremes"},{"time":332873,"text":"such as infiltrating standardization bodies"},{"time":336710,"text":"to sabotage encryption algorithms on purpose."},{"time":341458,"text":"And what that means"},{"time":343495,"text":"is that you take something which is secure,"},{"time":345315,"text":"an encryption algorithm which is so secure"},{"time":347736,"text":"that if you use that algorithm to encrypt one file,"},{"time":350843,"text":"nobody can decrypt that file."},{"time":352585,"text":"Even if they take every single computer on the planet just to decrypt that one file,"},{"time":356998,"text":"it's going to take millions of years."},{"time":359058,"text":"So that's basically perfectly safe, uncrackable."},{"time":361305,"text":"You take something which is that good"},{"time":363379,"text":"and then you weaken it on purpose,"},{"time":365863,"text":"making all of us less secure as an end result."},{"time":371473,"text":"A real-world equivalent would be that"},{"time":373604,"text":"intelligence agencies would force"},{"time":376256,"text":"some secret pin code into every single house alarm"},{"time":379083,"text":"so they could get into every single house"},{"time":380876,"text":"because, you know, bad people\nmight have house alarms,"},{"time":383122,"text":"but it will also make all of us"},{"time":385561,"text":"less secure as an end result."},{"time":387790,"text":"Backdooring encryption algorithms"},{"time":391530,"text":"just boggles the mind."},{"time":394626,"text":"But of course, these intelligence agencies\nare doing their job."},{"time":398401,"text":"This is what they have been told to do:"},{"time":400158,"text":"do signals intelligence,"},{"time":402388,"text":"monitor telecommunications,"},{"time":404400,"text":"monitor Internet traffic."},{"time":405822,"text":"That's what they're trying to do,"},{"time":407530,"text":"and since most, a very big part\nof the Internet traffic today is encrypted,"},{"time":410612,"text":"they're trying to find ways around the encryption."},{"time":412569,"text":"One way is to sabotage encryption algorithms,"},{"time":415626,"text":"which is a great example"},{"time":417511,"text":"about how U.S. intelligence agencies"},{"time":419732,"text":"are running loose."},{"time":421481,"text":"They are completely out of control,"},{"time":423322,"text":"and they should be brought back under control."}]},{"cues":[{"time":429629,"text":"So what do we actually know about the leaks?"},{"time":432579,"text":"Everything is based on the files"},{"time":434689,"text":"leaked by Mr. Snowden."},{"time":437187,"text":"The very first PRISM slides"},{"time":440035,"text":"from the beginning of June"},{"time":442024,"text":"detail a collection program where the data"},{"time":444118,"text":"is collected from service providers,"},{"time":445904,"text":"and they actually go and name the service providers"},{"time":448782,"text":"they have access to."},{"time":450113,"text":"They even have a specific date"},{"time":453055,"text":"on when the collection of data began"},{"time":455719,"text":"for each of the service providers."},{"time":457358,"text":"So for example, they name\nthe collection from Microsoft"},{"time":459645,"text":"started on September 11, 2007,"},{"time":463365,"text":"for Yahoo on the March 12, 2008,"},{"time":466097,"text":"and then others: Google, Facebook,"},{"time":469113,"text":"Skype, Apple and so on."}]},{"cues":[{"time":472357,"text":"And every single one of these companies denies."},{"time":475205,"text":"They all say that this simply isn't true,"},{"time":479600,"text":"that they are not giving\nbackdoor access to their data."},{"time":484208,"text":"Yet we have these files."},{"time":488331,"text":"So is one of the parties lying,"},{"time":490652,"text":"or is there some other alternative explanation?"},{"time":493975,"text":"And one explanation would be"},{"time":496897,"text":"that these parties, these service providers,"},{"time":499784,"text":"are not cooperating."},{"time":501700,"text":"Instead, they've been hacked."},{"time":504721,"text":"That would explain it. They aren't cooperating. They've been hacked."},{"time":507938,"text":"In this case, they've been hacked\nby their own government."},{"time":512116,"text":"That might sound outlandish,"},{"time":514537,"text":"but we already have cases where this has happened,"},{"time":516751,"text":"for example, the case of the Flame malware"},{"time":519797,"text":"which we strongly believe was authored"},{"time":521830,"text":"by the U.S. government,"},{"time":523727,"text":"and which, to spread, subverted the security"},{"time":527626,"text":"of the Windows Update network,"},{"time":530512,"text":"meaning here, the company was hacked"},{"time":534605,"text":"by their own government."},{"time":536963,"text":"And there's more evidence"},{"time":538562,"text":"supporting this theory as well."},{"time":541113,"text":"Der Spiegel, from Germany, leaked more information"},{"time":545118,"text":"about the operations run by the elite hacker units"},{"time":549383,"text":"operating inside these intelligence agencies."},{"time":552418,"text":"Inside NSA, the unit is called TAO,"},{"time":555044,"text":"Tailored Access Operations,"},{"time":556889,"text":"and inside GCHQ, which is the U.K. equivalent,"},{"time":560453,"text":"it's called NAC, Network Analysis Centre."},{"time":564452,"text":"And these recent leaks of these three slides"},{"time":568296,"text":"detail an operation"},{"time":570500,"text":"run by this GCHQ intelligence agency"},{"time":573658,"text":"from the United Kingdom"},{"time":575467,"text":"targeting a telecom here in Belgium."},{"time":579700,"text":"And what this really means"},{"time":581976,"text":"is that an E.U. country's intelligence agency"},{"time":585864,"text":"is breaching the security"},{"time":588079,"text":"of a telecom of a fellow E.U. country on purpose,"},{"time":592892,"text":"and they discuss it in their slides completely casually,"},{"time":596727,"text":"business as usual."},{"time":598328,"text":"Here's the primary target,"},{"time":599996,"text":"here's the secondary target,"},{"time":601374,"text":"here's the teaming."},{"time":602798,"text":"They probably have a team building\non Thursday evening in a pub."},{"time":606654,"text":"They even use cheesy PowerPoint clip art"},{"time":609695,"text":"like, you know, \"Success,\""},{"time":611402,"text":"when they gain access to services like this."},{"time":614666,"text":"What the hell?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":619685,"text":"And then there's the argument"},{"time":621518,"text":"that okay, yes, this might be going on,"},{"time":623178,"text":"but then again, other countries are doing it as well."},{"time":625815,"text":"All countries spy."},{"time":628238,"text":"And maybe that's true."},{"time":629976,"text":"Many countries spy, not all of them,\nbut let's take an example."},{"time":632414,"text":"Let's take, for example, Sweden."},{"time":634525,"text":"I'm speaking of Sweden because Sweden"},{"time":635901,"text":"has a little bit of a similar law to the United States."},{"time":638180,"text":"When your data traffic goes through Sweden,"},{"time":640303,"text":"their intelligence agency has a legal right by the law"},{"time":643113,"text":"to intercept that traffic."},{"time":645114,"text":"All right, how many Swedish decisionmakers"},{"time":648319,"text":"and politicians and business leaders"},{"time":651191,"text":"use, every day, U.S.-based services,"},{"time":654264,"text":"like, you know, run Windows or OSX,"},{"time":657532,"text":"or use Facebook or LinkedIn,"},{"time":659742,"text":"or store their data in clouds like iCloud"},{"time":663142,"text":"or Skydrive or DropBox,"},{"time":667036,"text":"or maybe use online services like\nAmazon web services or sales support?"},{"time":671339,"text":"And the answer is, every single Swedish\nbusiness leader does that every single day."},{"time":675296,"text":"And then we turn it around."},{"time":676895,"text":"How many American leaders"},{"time":678800,"text":"use Swedish webmails and cloud services?"},{"time":683093,"text":"And the answer is zero."},{"time":685133,"text":"So this is not balanced."},{"time":687402,"text":"It's not balanced by any means, not even close."}]},{"cues":[{"time":692027,"text":"And when we do have the occasional"},{"time":694468,"text":"European success story,"},{"time":696469,"text":"even those, then, typically end up being sold\nto the United States."},{"time":700035,"text":"Like, Skype used to be secure."},{"time":702299,"text":"It used to be end-to-end encrypted."},{"time":705032,"text":"Then it was sold to the United States."},{"time":707073,"text":"Today, it no longer is secure."},{"time":709722,"text":"So once again, we take something which is secure"},{"time":712943,"text":"and then we make it less secure on purpose,"},{"time":714813,"text":"making all of us less secure as an outcome."}]},{"cues":[{"time":720855,"text":"And then the argument that the United States"},{"time":723102,"text":"is only fighting terrorists."},{"time":725120,"text":"It's the war on terror."},{"time":726286,"text":"You shouldn't worry about it."},{"time":728833,"text":"Well, it's not the war on terror."},{"time":731063,"text":"Yes, part of it is war on terror, and yes,"},{"time":733236,"text":"there are terrorists, and they do kill and maim,"},{"time":736212,"text":"and we should fight them,"},{"time":737763,"text":"but we know through these leaks"},{"time":739369,"text":"that they have used the same techniques"},{"time":741951,"text":"to listen to phone calls of European leaders,"},{"time":745287,"text":"to tap the email of residents of Mexico and Brazil,"},{"time":748742,"text":"to read email traffic inside the United Nations Headquarters and E.U. Parliament,"},{"time":753548,"text":"and I don't think they are trying to find terrorists"},{"time":756702,"text":"from inside the E.U. Parliament, right?"},{"time":759720,"text":"It's not the war on terror."},{"time":761668,"text":"Part of it might be, and there are terrorists,"},{"time":765810,"text":"but are we really thinking about terrorists"},{"time":768237,"text":"as such an existential threat"},{"time":770406,"text":"that we are willing to do anything at all to fight them?"},{"time":774082,"text":"Are the Americans ready\nto throw away the Constituion"},{"time":777573,"text":"and throw it in the trash\njust because there are terrorists?"},{"time":781814,"text":"And the same thing with the Bill of Rights\nand all the amendments"},{"time":784338,"text":"and the Universal Declaration of Human Rights"},{"time":786655,"text":"and the E.U. conventions on human rights\nand fundamental freedoms"},{"time":791806,"text":"and the press freedom?"},{"time":793323,"text":"Do we really think terrorism\nis such an existential threat,"},{"time":797138,"text":"we are ready to do anything at all?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":802490,"text":"But people are scared about terrorists,"},{"time":805154,"text":"and then they think that\nmaybe that surveillance is okay"},{"time":807568,"text":"because they have nothing to hide."},{"time":809612,"text":"Feel free to survey me if that helps."},{"time":812319,"text":"And whoever tells you that they have nothing to hide"},{"time":815207,"text":"simply hasn't thought about this long enough."}]},{"cues":[{"time":822520,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":828385,"text":"Because we have this thing called privacy,"},{"time":831157,"text":"and if you really think that you have nothing to hide,"},{"time":833502,"text":"please make sure that's the first thing you tell me,"},{"time":835718,"text":"because then I know"},{"time":837268,"text":"that I should not trust you with any secrets,"},{"time":838908,"text":"because obviously you can't keep a secret."},{"time":845065,"text":"But people are brutally honest with the Internet,"},{"time":848894,"text":"and when these leaks started,"},{"time":851590,"text":"many people were asking me about this."},{"time":853468,"text":"And I have nothing to hide."},{"time":855042,"text":"I'm not doing anything bad or anything illegal."},{"time":858332,"text":"Yet, I have nothing that I would in particular"},{"time":861117,"text":"like to share with an intelligence agency,"},{"time":863910,"text":"especially a foreign intelligence agency."},{"time":868047,"text":"And if we indeed need a Big Brother,"},{"time":870902,"text":"I would much rather have a domestic Big Brother"},{"time":874380,"text":"than a foreign Big Brother."},{"time":877545,"text":"And when the leaks started,\nthe very first thing I tweeted about this"},{"time":882604,"text":"was a comment about how,"},{"time":884678,"text":"when you've been using search engines,"},{"time":886366,"text":"you've been potentially leaking all that\nto U.S. intelligence."},{"time":890015,"text":"And two minutes later, I got a reply"},{"time":891987,"text":"by somebody called Kimberly from the United States"},{"time":894323,"text":"challenging me, like, why am I worried about this?"},{"time":896503,"text":"What am I sending to worry about this?\nAm I sending naked pictures or something?"},{"time":900535,"text":"And my answer to Kimberly was"},{"time":902503,"text":"that what I'm sending is none of your business,"},{"time":905532,"text":"and it should be none\nof your government's business either."},{"time":909797,"text":"Because that's what it's about. It's about privacy."},{"time":912049,"text":"Privacy is nonnegotiable."},{"time":913963,"text":"It should be built in to all the systems we use."}]},{"cues":[{"time":919968,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":926830,"text":"And one thing we should all understand"},{"time":929449,"text":"is that we are brutally honest with search engines."},{"time":934048,"text":"You show me your search history,"},{"time":936799,"text":"and I'll find something incriminating"},{"time":939165,"text":"or something embarrassing there in five minutes."},{"time":942602,"text":"We are more honest with search engines"},{"time":944390,"text":"than we are with our families."},{"time":946152,"text":"Search engines know more about you"},{"time":948243,"text":"than your family members know about you."},{"time":951009,"text":"And this is all the kind\nof information we are giving away,"},{"time":954097,"text":"we are giving away to the United States."}]},{"cues":[{"time":958472,"text":"And surveillance changes history."},{"time":960950,"text":"We know this through examples\nof corrupt presidents like Nixon."},{"time":964159,"text":"Imagine if he would have had the kind\nof surveillance tools that are available today."},{"time":968631,"text":"And let me actually quote"},{"time":970940,"text":"the president of Brazil, Ms. Dilma Rousseff."},{"time":974073,"text":"She was one of the targets of NSA surveillance."},{"time":977359,"text":"Her email was read, and she spoke"},{"time":979635,"text":"at the United Nations Headquarters, and she said,"},{"time":982658,"text":"\"If there is no right to privacy,"},{"time":984671,"text":"there can be no true freedom\nof expression and opinion,"},{"time":987498,"text":"and therefore, there can be no effective democracy.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":992609,"text":"That's what it's about."},{"time":994954,"text":"Privacy is the building block of our democracies."},{"time":1000611,"text":"And to quote a fellow security researcher, Marcus Ranum,"},{"time":1004076,"text":"he said that the United States\nis right now treating the Internet"},{"time":1007903,"text":"as it would be treating one of its colonies."},{"time":1010996,"text":"So we are back to the age of colonization,"},{"time":1013561,"text":"and we, the foreign users of the Internet,"},{"time":1016623,"text":"we should think about Americans as our masters."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1023005,"text":"So Mr. Snowden, he's been blamed for many things."},{"time":1026980,"text":"Some are blaming him for causing problems"},{"time":1029634,"text":"for the U.S. cloud industry\nand software companies with these revelations --"},{"time":1032825,"text":"and blaming Snowden for causing problems\nfor the U.S. cloud industry"},{"time":1037121,"text":"would be the equivalent of blaming Al Gore"},{"time":1039580,"text":"for causing global warming."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1041897,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1044151,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1051853,"text":"So, what is there to be done?"},{"time":1058061,"text":"Should we worry. No, we shouldn't worry."},{"time":1059841,"text":"We should be angry, because this is wrong,"},{"time":1062277,"text":"and it's rude, and it should not be done."},{"time":1065016,"text":"But that's not going to really change the situation."},{"time":1067284,"text":"What's going to change the situation\nfor the rest of the world"},{"time":1070505,"text":"is to try to steer away"},{"time":1072787,"text":"from systems built in the United States."},{"time":1075420,"text":"And that's much easier said than done."},{"time":1078050,"text":"How do you do that?"},{"time":1079759,"text":"A single country, any single country in Europe"},{"time":1081558,"text":"cannot replace and build replacements"},{"time":1084351,"text":"for the U.S.-made operating systems\nand cloud services."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1087113,"text":"But maybe you don't have to do it alone."},{"time":1089006,"text":"Maybe you can do it together with other countries."},{"time":1090775,"text":"The solution is open source."},{"time":1094271,"text":"By building together open, free, secure systems,"},{"time":1099884,"text":"we can go around such surveillance,"},{"time":1102992,"text":"and then one country doesn't have\nto solve the problem by itself."},{"time":1106215,"text":"It only has to solve one little problem."},{"time":1108687,"text":"And to quote a fellow security researcher, Haroon Meer,"},{"time":1114210,"text":"one country only has to make a small wave,"},{"time":1117179,"text":"but those small waves together become a tide,"},{"time":1120646,"text":"and the tide will lift all the boats up at the same time,"},{"time":1124266,"text":"and the tide we will build"},{"time":1125917,"text":"with secure, free, open-source systems,"},{"time":1129358,"text":"will become the tide that will lift all of us"},{"time":1131757,"text":"up and above the surveillance state."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1137339,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1139451,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}